gration primary outcome, none reporting adverse effects, and no consistent results on relevant outcomes across domains. Authors' conclusions emphasized no consistently significant benefit for focused therapeutic interventions compared with standard services, common services not rigorously evaluated, need for more robust evaluation including comparison with no intervention, and additional research needed in LMICs."}
